\n\t\t\tSome accessibility issues may have multiple success criterion apply to them. We have identified the one most relevant for each checklist item.\n\t\t

\n\t\t

\n\t\t\tDoes this checklist guarantee my site is accessible?\n\t\t

\n\t\t

\n\t\t\tNo. However, addressing the issues called out in this checklist will help improve the experience for everyone who uses your site.\n\t\t

\n\t\t

\n\t\t\tThe issues this checklist prompts you to check for covers a wide range of disability conditions. There is no such thing as “perfect accessibility” or a site being “100% accessible.” You should be wary of companies and services that make such promises. If you need professional accessibility help, use professional accessibility services.\n\t\t
